canonical:
  title: 謝報諭表
  author: 林存
  language: lzh
  text: 奮張王旅立無敵之神功遠遣使軺諭非常之懿事恩榮有異感抃無從中謝 皇帝天縱英謀日躋聖德必勝必取用睿略之縱橫自北自南致土疆之開拓華夷盡服號令惟新念玆藩屛之邦首辱絲綸之命申加錫予曲示撫存顧自昧於報酬惟益深於慶賴
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝報諭表
  author: 林存
  language: lzh
  text: 奮張王旅。立無敵之神功。遠遣使軺。諭非常之懿事。恩榮有異。感抃無從。中謝。 皇帝天縱英謀。日躋聖德。必勝必取。用睿略之縱橫。自北自南。致土疆之開拓。華夷盡服。號令惟新。念玆藩屛之邦。首辱絲綸之命。申加錫予。曲示撫存。顧自昧於報酬。惟益深於慶賴。
korean:
  title: 사보유표
  author: 임존
  language: kor
  text: |-
    분연(奮然)히 왕사(王師)를 일으켜 무적(無敵)의 신공(神功)을 세우시고, 멀리 사절을 보내어 비상한 아름다운 일을 조유(詔諭)하시니, 은영(恩榮)이 특이하온지라 감격하여 춤추옵나이다. 중사(中謝)
    황제께옵서 하늘이 내신 영모(英謀)로 날이 갈수록 성덕(聖德)에 오르시어 전쟁하면 반드시 이기고, 공격하면 반드시 빼앗도록 지혜로운 군략(軍略)을 종횡으로 지휘하시고, 북으로나 남으로나 강토를 활짝 개척하시니 화이(華夷)가 다 복종하고 호령이 새삼 새롭도소이다.이 번병(藩屛)의 나라를 생각하시어 첫머리로 윤음(綸音)을 내리시되 각별히 하사(下賜)를 더하시고 간곡히 어루만져 주시니, 돌아봄에 스스로 보답할 방법에 어두워 오직 경하(慶賀)하는 마음만 더욱 깊을 뿐이옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0380_010_0210&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude for the Imperial Proclamation
  author: Lim Jon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    With fierce resolve, the royal armies surge forth, establishing deeds of invincible prowess. From afar, emissaries are dispatched to proclaim these extraordinary and glorious affairs. Such unparalleled grace and honor stir the heart to dance with gratitude.

    [Middle Expression of Thanks]

    Your Majesty, endowed by Heaven with brilliant strategy, ascends each day to greater sagacity. In battle, victory is assured; in conquest, triumph is certain. Through wise military craft wielded with supreme flexibility, from north to south the realm expands, territories unfold like blossoming flowers. Chinese and barbarian alike submit; the imperial edicts shine ever new and bright.

    Thinking upon this vassal state, you first bestow upon us the grace of the imperial word, granting additional favors with special care, and tending to us with gentle solicitude. Yet looking back upon myself, I find myself at a loss for words of repayment. I can only deepen my heart's reverence and gratitude.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'middle expression of thanks' (中謝) marks a structural division in this memorial, transitioning from gratitude for imperial favor to acknowledgment of the emperor's virtues and a renewed expression of loyalty.
  - key: ''
    value: The phrase 'from north to south' reflects the imperial expansion and unification efforts characteristic of the period in which this memorial was composed.
